The paper discusses the use of compressive sensing for spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which involves signal processing, information theory, and network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for decision-making, which falls under cs.MM (Machine Learning) and cs.LG (Learning).
